BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EQG3QtRtvvQUI__D78SVH
SUMMARY:Youth Clowning with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260404T233132Z
DTSTART:20260420T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Unleash your silly side! A playful\\\, youth-friendly class usi
	ng improv\\\, physical comedy\\\, and clown games to build confidence & cr
	eativity\\n\\n\\n\\nGet ready to unleash your silly side! This series is a
	ll about having fun\\\, taking creative risks\\\, and finding the funny in
	 the unexpected. Working as a group to start\\\, participants will dive he
	ad-over-heels into ensemble theater\\\, improvisation\\\, physical comedy\
	\\, and clown-inspired games\\\, learning how to turn everyday moments int
	o laugh-out-loud comedy. Whether you’re interested in performing or just w
	ant to break out of your comfort zone\\\, this session is all about embrac
	ing play\\\, thinking on your feet\\\, and making bold comedic choices. No
	 experience? No problem! Just bring your imagination\\\, a sense of humor\
	\\, and a willingness to get ridiculous. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (6)
	 Monday classes \\nTime: 4:00 pm to 5:20 pm \\nLocation: The Clown Garage 
	at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issa
